library(tidyverse)
library(ggridges)

load the weather data

weather_df = 
  rnoaa::meteo_pull_monitors(
    c("USW00094728", "USW00022534", "USS0023B17S"),
    var = c("PRCP", "TMIN", "TMAX"), 
    date_min = "2021-01-01",
    date_max = "2022-12-31") |>
  mutate(
    name = recode(
      id, 
      USW00094728 = "CentralPark_NY", 
      USC00519397 = "Molokai_HI",
      USS0023B17S = "Waterhole_WA"),
    tmin = tmin / 10,
    tmax = tmax / 10) |>
  select(name, id, everything())

  geom_point()

Advanced scatterplot

  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)

* alpha=tmin adjust transparency-left is more transparent than right * alpha=tmax adjust transparency-down is more transparent than up *alpha=0.2, setup in geom_point() to serve as a global option,transparency =0.2

combine some elements and plot them

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = date, y = tmax, color = name)) + 
  geom_point(aes(size = prcp), alpha = .5) +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) + 
  facet_grid(. ~ name)

some small notes

you can have whatever geoms you want.

  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, y = tmin)) + 
  geom_hex()#蜂巢
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_binhex()`).

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, y = tmin)) + 
  geom_bin2d()#square
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_bin2d()`).

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, y = tmin)) + 
  geom_density2d()#等线图

let’s try a new geomtry

weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, fill = name)) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.3, adjust=0.5) 
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_density()`).

density plot will lose some information(little bumps),using adjust may help rescue
